---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for B2B and Wholesale in 2026';
const description = 'A practical shortlist of Shopify email apps for wholesale buyers, account-aware messaging, reorder cycles, and sales-assisted ecommerce.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','B2B teams with rich account data','Useful for segmentation, account behavior, and long consideration cycles.','B2B identity and pricing data need careful integration.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Wholesale brands with repeat catalog orders','A commerce-focused option for reorder and product communication.','Complex account-specific rules may require extra work.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/automations/'],['Sequenzy','Lean wholesale nurture','Good for onboarding, product education, and reorder sequences.','Confirm account and quote workflow support.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Sales and marketing teams sharing a platform','Useful for campaigns, automation, and transactional communication.','B2B commerce context may need connectors.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small wholesale operations','A simple starting point for account announcements and catalog updates.','Limited account-level personalization.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">B2B email needs more than a consumer campaign sent to a business address. Buyers may have account pricing, approval steps, multiple stakeholders, and predictable reorder cycles.</p><p>Measure qualified reorder activity, account engagement, sales-assisted conversion, average order value, and support burden. Protect account-specific pricing and avoid exposing wholesale offers to the wrong identity or segment.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for B2B and wholesale</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is a candidate when it can distinguish account context from individual engagement, trigger useful reorder and education messages, and hand high-intent activity to sales when needed. Start with identity resolution, permissions, and pricing rules before expanding the campaign calendar; B2B mistakes are often more expensive than consumer mistakes.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Review current contacts, users, events, automation, and integration costs; account-level data can change implementation scope.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Account identity</td><td>Reliable customer and company data</td><td>Qualified account activity</td></tr><tr><td>Reorders</td><td>Catalog and purchase cadence</td><td>Repeat wholesale orders</td></tr><tr><td>Sales handoff</td><td>Intent events and ownership</td><td>Sales-assisted conversion</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Read <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, explore <a href="/for/b2b-wholesale">B2B use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
